 • CatBoost dominant model (88% weight in Ridge blender)\")\nprint(\"   • Tree models capture complex non-linear relationships\")\nprint(\"   • Linear Ridge less effective (negative weight in blender)\")\n\nprint(\"\\n7. BUSINESS RECOMMENDATIONS:\")\nprint(\"   Energy Efficiency Interventions:\")\nprint(\"     → Prioritize insulation upgrades for old buildings\")\nprint(\"     → Focus on buildings with high occupancy density\")\nprint(\"     → Consider HVAC upgrades in extreme climate zones\")\nprint(\"   \")\nprint(\"   Forecasting & Planning:\")\nprint(\"     → Weather (temp, HDD, CDD) critical for load forecasting\")\nprint(\"     → Seasonal patterns captured by degree days\")\nprint(\"     → Monitor occupancy changes for anomaly detection\")\nprint(\"   \")\nprint(\"   Data Collection Priorities:\")\nprint(\"     → Ensure reliable temperature measurements\")\nprint(\"     → Track building insulation quality\")\nprint(\"     → Monitor occupancy patterns\")\n\nprint(\"\\n8. MODEL TRUSTWORTHINESS:\")\nprint(\"   ✓ Feature importance consistent across multiple methods\")\nprint(\"   ✓ Relationships align with domain knowledge (thermodynamics)\")\nprint(\"   ✓ SHAP analysis confirms model reasoning is physically sound\")\nprint(\"   ✓ No unexpected or suspicious patterns detected\")\nprint(\"   ✓ Individual predictions explainable to stakeholders\")\nprint(\"   ✓ Model ready for deployment with monitoring\")\n\nprint(\"\\n9. LESSONS LEARNED:\")\nprint(\"   • Simpler models can outperform complex ensembles (CatBoost alone)\")\nprint(\"   • Blending improvements must be validated on holdout data\")\nprint(\"   • Small OOF improvements (~0.004 RMSE) may not generalize\")\nprint(\"   • Distribution shift affects complex models more\")\nprint(\"   • XAI reveals why CatBoost succeeds (captures key physics)\")\n\nprint(\"\\n\" + \"=\"*80)","metadata":{"trusted":true},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Part 6: Generate Submission Files\n---","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# --- Create final submission file\n\nsubmission_catboost_only = pd.DataFrame({\n    'id': test['id'],\n    'energy_consumption': np.clip(test_cb, 0, None)\n})\nsubmission_catboost_only.to_csv('submission_catboost_only.csv', index=False)\n\nprint(\"  • submission_catboost_only.csv (CatBoost-only)\")\n\nprint(\"\\nSubmission preview (submission_catboost_only):\")\nprint(submission_catboost_only.head(10))\nprint(f\"\\nMean predicted consumption (CB-only): {submission_catboost_only['energy_consumption'].mean():.2f} kWh\")\nprint(f\"Std predicted consumption (CB-only): {submission_catboost_only['energy_consumption'].std():.2f} kWh\")\nprint(f\"Min predicted consumption (CB-only): {submission_catboost_only['energy_consumption'].min():.2f} kWh\")\nprint(f\"Max predicted consumption (CB-only): {submission_catboost_only['energy_consumption'].max():.2f} kWh\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-02-10T20:34:11.286351Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-02-10T20:34:11.286785Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-02-10T20:34:11.323932Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-02-10T20:34:11.286756Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-02-10T20:34:11.323099Z"}},"outputs":[],"execution_count":null},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"---\n## Conclusion\n---\n\n### What we accomplished:\n\n#### 1. Model Development \n- Nested cross-validation prevents data leakage\n- Hyperparameter tuning optimizes each model\n- Multiple ensemble strategies explored\n- Out-of-fold predictions for unbiased evaluation\n\n#### 2. XAI Analysis \n- **Feature Importance** from multiple methods (tree-based, permutation)\n- **Partial Dependence Plots** showing average feature effects\n- **SHAP Analysis** providing:\n  - Global feature importance (summary plots)\n  - Individual prediction explanations (waterfall/force plots)\n  - Feature relationships (dependence plots)\n  - Interaction effects (interaction heatmap)\n\n#### 3. Validated Model Behavior \n- Feature importance consistent across methods\n- Relationships align with domain knowledge (thermodynamics)\n- NMAR indicators successfully capture missingness patterns\n- Model reasoning is transparent and interpretable\n\n#### 4. Business Insights \n- Identified key drivers of energy consumption\n- Prioritized interventions for energy efficiency\n- Established data collection priorities\n- Provided framework for model monitoring\n\n\n### Final Model Recommendation:\n\nBased on test set performance:\n- **CatBoost standalone**: 11.599 RMSE  **BEST**\n- Ridge blender (4 models): 11.604 RMSE\n- Ridge blender (2 models): 11.609 RMSE\n\n**Winner:** CatBoost standalone\n\n**Reasons:**\n1. Simplest (fewer degrees of freedom)\n2. Most robust to distribution shift\n3. Easiest to maintain and explain\n4. Blending gains (~0.004 RMSE) within noise\n\n### Next Steps:\n\n**Deployment:**\n1. Deploy CatBoost model to production\n2. Set up monitoring for key features\n\n**Monitoring:**\n1. Track feature distributions over time\n2. Alert on distribution shifts\n3. Monitor prediction errors by building type\n4. Retrain periodically with new data\n\n**Research:**\n1. Collect more granular temporal data\n2. Test on other building types/regions\n\n\n**Team Members:** Noelani Bradley (ID: 77202019116), Karina Azizova (ID: 77201898228), Itzel Hernandez Gonzalez (ID: 77202857743), Diren Düzgüner (ID: 77211868869)\n\n**Date:** February 2026\n\n**Course:** Data Science Project\n\n---","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"markdown","source":"## Resources\n\n- https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/data-analysis/what-is-exploratory-data-analysis/\n- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n_ZMQj09S6w\n- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wQt4kgAOgV0&t\n- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Q_xa4RvnDcY&t\n- https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XXFLFWHP9Nc\n- https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Occam%27s_razor\n- AI Assistance\n\nClaude AI. (2025–2026, December–February). Personal communication regarding machine learning implementa